cells.cleanedText: TYC acquires JCI (and becomes new JCI)
McGraw Hill Financial, Inc. rebrands as S&P Global, Inc.
Global Payments is acquiring Heartland Payment Systems
JAB Holding Company acquired Keurig Green Mountain
ACE Limited changes name to Chubb Limited
WSH merges with TW (and renames to WLTW)
Allergan acquired by Actavis plc (and changed name to Allergan, pl.
PetSmart acquired by private equity consortium
Safeway acquired by private equity consortium
Life Technologies acquired by Thermo Fisher Scientific Inc
Allegion spun off by Ingersoll Rand
Dell acquired by private equity consortium
Softbank consortium purchase results in public float below 50%
Apollo Group's market cap more representative of a mid-cap
DF too small after spinoff of White Wave Foods
A majority of MetroPCS was acquired by T-Mobile
ABBV spun off from Abbott Labs (ABT)
TIE acquired by Precision Cast Parts (PCP)
Expedia Inc. spun off TripAdvisor Inc.
Nicor acquired by AGL, which retained the GAS ticker.
Janus Capital Groups market capitalization is less than $1.2 billion and is no longer representative of the large cap market space.
Marshall & Iisley is being bought by Bank of Montreal
Alpha Natural Resources is acquiring Massey Energy in a deal expected to be completed on or about that date pending final approvals.
Company split. QEP retained, but ticker changed.
